Package abstractDataTypesImplemented

Class IntegerUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph

java.lang.Object
abstractDataTypesImplemented.IntegerUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
GraphADT<java.lang.Integer>
public class IntegerUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements GraphADT<java.lang.Integer>
This class is the implementation of GraphADT that uses Integers as the base type. The vertex is the element and it's index is itself. That's why it's an indexed graph, this is not using references, it's using values for retrieving the vertex. The graph is undirected and it uses an adjacency list.
Author:
Borja Moralejo Tobajas
